  <reg:acttitle>Forestry Service Providers Protection Act</reg:acttitle>
  <reg:title>Forestry Service Providers Compensation Fund Regulation</reg:title>
  <reg:amsincluded>[includes amendments up to B.C. Reg. 286/2016, December 7, 2016]</reg:amsincluded>
  <reg:regpitid>64_2012_pit</reg:regpitid>
  <reg:content>
    <bcl:section id="d2e33" toc="false">
      <bcl:marginalnote>Definitions</bcl:marginalnote>
      <bcl:num>1</bcl:num>
      <bcl:text>In this regulation:</bcl:text>
      <bcl:definition id="d3e63">
        <bcl:text>
          <in:term>Act</in:term> means the <bcl:link resource="leg" xlink:href="/legislation/10016_01" xlink:type="locator"><in:doc>Forestry Service Providers Protection Act</in:doc></bcl:link>;</bcl:text>
      </bcl:definition>
      <bcl:definition id="d4e63">
        <bcl:text>
          <in:term>free growing stand</in:term> has the same meaning as in the <bcl:link resource="leg" xlink:href="/legislation/02069_01" xlink:type="locator"><in:doc>Forest and Range Practices Act</in:doc></bcl:link>.</bcl:text>
      </bcl:definition>
      <bcl:hnote>[en. B.C. Reg. 286/2016, s. 1.]</bcl:hnote>
    </bcl:section>
    <bcl:section id="d2e51">
      <bcl:marginalnote>Fund established</bcl:marginalnote>
      <bcl:num>2</bcl:num>
      <bcl:text>For the purposes set out in section 26 (1) of the Act, the Forestry Service Providers Compensation Fund is established with an initial balance of $5 million, as provided by the government.</bcl:text>
    </bcl:section>
    <bcl:section id="d2e63">
      <bcl:marginalnote>Forestry service providers</bcl:marginalnote>
      <bcl:num>3</bcl:num>
      <bcl:subsection id="d2e71">
        <bcl:num>1</bcl:num>
        <bcl:text>For the purposes of the definition of "services" in section 1 (1) of the Act, the following are prescribed:</bcl:text>
        <bcl:paragraph id="d3e83">
          <bcl:num>a</bcl:num>
          <bcl:text>activities relating to growing seedlings;</bcl:text>
        </bcl:paragraph>
        <bcl:paragraph id="d4e83">
          <bcl:num>b</bcl:num>
          <bcl:text>silviculture activities that are necessary, or are required under the <bcl:link resource="leg" xlink:href="/legislation/02069_01" xlink:type="locator"><in:doc>Forest and Range Practices Act</in:doc></bcl:link>, to establish free growing stands.</bcl:text>
        </bcl:paragraph>
      </bcl:subsection>
      <bcl:subsection id="d2e83">
        <bcl:num>2</bcl:num>
        <bcl:text>For the purposes of Part 2 of the Act, the class of persons who provide services for a holder of an agreement referred to in section 12 of the <bcl:link resource="leg" xlink:href="/legislation/96157_00" xlink:type="locator"><in:doc>Forest Act</in:doc></bcl:link> are designated as forestry service providers.</bcl:text>
      </bcl:subsection>
      <bcl:hnote>[en. B.C. Reg. 3/2013, s. 2; am. B.C. Reg. 286/2016, s. 2.]</bcl:hnote>
    </bcl:section>
    <reg:provisionsnote>[Provisions relevant to the enactment of this regulation: <bcl:link resource="leg" xlink:href="/legislation/10016_01" xlink:type="locator"><in:doc>Forestry Service Providers Protection Act</in:doc></bcl:link>, S.B.C. 2010, c. 16, section 35]</reg:provisionsnote>
  </reg:content>
